# Safe Order — Implementation Plan

## 1. Overview

**Safe Order** is an Algerian e-commerce security platform that solves the 30-45% delivery return rate problem through:
- **Safe Pay**: Smart deposit system — customer pays upfront, deducted at delivery
- **Safe Track**: Real-time package tracking
- **Safe Standards**: Mandatory quality conditions for merchants
- **Safe Insights**: AI analytics on return causes
- **Trust Score**: Reputation scoring for merchants, customers, and couriers

**Primary color**: `#0080ff` (blue from logo). Supporting palette: Navy `#0D3B66`, Green `#0D6E3F`, Gold `#F0AE1A`.

---

## 2. Architecture

```
┌─────────────────────┐         ┌─────────────────────┐
│   Frontend (React)  │  REST   │  Backend (FastAPI)   │
│   Vercel (free)     │◄───────►│  Railway (free)      │
│   TypeScript + CSS  │         │  Python 3.11+        │
└─────────────────────┘         └──────────┬──────────┘
                                           │
                                    ┌──────▼──────┐
                                    │  PostgreSQL  │
                                    │  Railway     │
                                    └─────────────┘
```

### Tech Stack (per SRS)
| Layer | Technology |
|-------|-----------|
| Frontend | React 18 + TypeScript + Vite |
| Styling | CSS Modules (minimalistic, professional — NOT Tailwind per user request) |
| Backend | Python FastAPI |
| Database | PostgreSQL (via SQLAlchemy + Alembic) |
| Auth | JWT (access 15min + httpOnly refresh) + simulated SMS OTP |
| Payments | Simulated CIB/Dahabia/BaridiMob gateway |
| AI/ML Models | Python scripts in `/backend/models/` |
| Hosting | Vercel (frontend), Railway (backend + DB) |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The SRS specifies Tailwind CSS, but the user explicitly asked for **minimalistic design that does NOT look AI-generated** with **vanilla CSS / CSS Modules**. I will use clean CSS with a professional design system instead of Tailwind.

---

## 3. Phased Execution Plan

I will build this **one step at a time**, waiting for your approval between each step.

### Step 1: Project Scaffolding & Backend Foundation
- Initialize `/frontend` (Vite + React + TypeScript)
- Initialize `/backend` (FastAPI project structure)
- Create `.env` and `.env.example` files
- Set up database models (SQLAlchemy) for all entities
- Set up Alembic migrations

### Step 2: Authentication & User Management
- Merchant registration (with simulated OTP)
- Customer identification (by phone, no password — simulated OTP)
- JWT auth system (access + refresh tokens)
- RBAC: Customer / Merchant / Admin roles
- Admin seeded account
- Safe Standards acceptance flow

### Step 3: Order Pipeline & Core Business Logic
- Order creation (via unique customer link)
- 6-category pipeline: Confirmation → Preparation → Dispatch → Delivery → Delivered → Return Processed
- Smart Badges: Safe Pay / New / Loyal / Risk
- Order status transitions
- Tracking code generation

### Step 4: Safe Pay — Simulated Payment System
- Simulated CIB / Dahabia / BaridiMob payment gateway
- Deposit blocking, deduction at delivery, refund on return
- Payment status tracking
- Wallet / financial history for customers

### Step 5: Safe Track — Real-Time Tracking
- Step-by-step timeline per order
- Status updates from merchant side
- Customer remark system
- Simulated delivery company integration

### Step 6: Feedback, Trust Score & Safe Insights
- Post-delivery feedback (1-5 stars, criteria, comment)
- Trust Score calculation (0-100)
- Risk Flag computation
- `/backend/models/` — AI analysis scripts:
  - `return_analyzer.py` — Identifies return causes from order + feedback data
  - `recommendation_engine.py` — Personalized recommendations for merchants
  - `risk_predictor.py` — Non-pickup risk prediction

### Step 7: Merchant Dashboard Frontend
- Dashboard with 6-category pipeline
- Order details with badges
- Statistics page (delivery rate, return rate, Trust Score, best sellers)
- Safe Insights page (AI analysis results)
- Tracking label print (PDF generation)
- Safe Standards onboarding

### Step 8: Customer Interface Frontend
- Order sheet via unique link (no account required)
- Safe Pay payment flow
- Cart (active orders)
- Safe Track timeline
- Feedback form
- Wallet / purchase history

### Step 9: Admin Portal
- Standards validation
- User management
- Global dashboard with platform metrics
- Dispute/moderation interface

### Step 10: i18n (Arabic, French, English)
- Translation system with RTL support for Arabic
- Language selector on home page
- All UI strings externalized

### Step 11: Testing & Demo Setup
- Seeded demo data (merchants, customers, orders in various states)
- Test accounts with pre-configured scenarios
- Demo shortcuts (skip OTP, instant payment, fast-forward order states)
- Testing guide document

### Step 12: Deployment Guide
- `DEPLOYMENT.md` with step-by-step instructions
- Vercel configuration
- Railway configuration (backend + PostgreSQL)
- Environment variables mapping
- Testing instructions for the jury

---

## 4. Database Schema (Key Entities)

| Table | Key Fields |
|-------|-----------|
| `users` | id, role (merchant/customer/admin), first_name, last_name, phone, email, wilaya, municipality, address, trust_score, is_verified, language |
| `merchant_profiles` | user_id, delivery_companies[], safe_standards_accepted, store_name |
| `orders` | id, merchant_id, customer_id, tracking_code, status (6 states), badge, product_name, product_description, product_photos[], price, safe_pay_amount, delivery_fee, remaining_amount, delivery_company, remark, created_at |
| `payments` | id, order_id, customer_id, amount, method (CIB/Dahabia/BaridiMob), status (pending/confirmed/refunded), type (deposit/delivery) |
| `tracking_events` | id, order_id, status, timestamp, note |
| `feedbacks` | id, order_id, customer_id, merchant_id, rating (1-5), criteria[], comment |
| `return_analyses` | id, order_id, cause, recommendation, created_at |
| `safe_academy` | id, title, type (video/article/podcast), url, theme, language |

---

## 5. Simulated Services (for Demo)

| Service | Real | Demo Simulation |
|---------|------|-----------------|
| SMS OTP | Twilio | Always accepts code `123456` |
| CIB Payment | CIB Gateway | Instant success with any card `4111...` |
| Dahabia | Algeria Post | Instant success with any card number |
| BaridiMob | BaridiMob API | Instant success with any account |
| Delivery Tracking | Yalidine/ZR Express API | Backend auto-advances status on timer |
| Push Notifications | Firebase | Console log + in-app notification |

